This paper deals with the design of transmission schemes for cache-enabled multigroup multicasting networks, which involves the coordination of cloud and edge processing to minimize delivery latency. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), systems and control (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these are the five most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
